<h2 class="subhead">Financial support for all students</h2><div style="clear:both;"><h2>How to apply for student support</h2>If you live in Knowsley and currently 
attend a Knowsley school, sixth form 
or Community College, you should have 
received a PN1 application form when 
we came to talk to students about 
higher education financial support.  
Please 
contact us using the details at the 
bottom of this page if you have not 
received a form or you can apply 
online via Student Finance Direct(see 
related links).<br />
<br />
You will be required to submit your 
passport or original birth certificate 
in order to verify your identity. We 
will also need a declaration from a 
person that knows you if you submit 
your birth certificate.<br />
<br />
</div>
<div style="clear:both;"><ul><li>where you live</li>
<li>whether you have been in higher 
education before</li>
<li>whether your course is eligible</li>
<li>your residence in the UK</li>
<li>whether you can be classed as an 
independent student</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div style="clear:both;"><h2>Application deadlines</h2>Closing date for continuing students is 
25 May 2007.  <br />
<br />
Closing date for new students is 30 
June 2007.<br />
<br />
Completed application forms should be 
sent to your Local Education Authority 
who will check the initial 
application.  You can access the 
application via the DfES Student 
Support website (see related links 
below).  We strongly recommend that you 
return your application form as soon as 
possible.  If you do not meet the 
deadline your first instalment of 
student loan may be delayed as the 
volume of applications received means 
that it takes approximately four to six 
weeks 
to process your application.<br />
<br />
If, after your course starts, you 
decide that you want to apply for 
financial help, you must apply no 
later than nine months after the first 
day of the academic year of your 
course.  Therefore if your course 
starts in Autumn 2007, you have until 
31 May 2008 to apply.<br />
<br />
</div>
<div style="clear:both;"><h2>Maintenance loans</h2>Eligible students aged under 60 can 
apply for a loan to cover living costs 
such as accommodation, food, clothes, 
travel etc.  The amount of loan payable 
depends on the criteria outlined above.<br />
<br />
The Student Loans Company will pay the 
maintenance loan in three instalments, 
one at the start of each term. Loans 
must be repaid after you leave 
university and when you are earning 
over &pound;15,000 a year.<br />
<br />
The table below shows the maximum 
amount of loan for students in a full 
year of study and the final year of 
study.<br />
<br />
</div>
